Note that $(1,3)$ and $(3,4)$ are two points on the line, so the line has a direction vector of
\[\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}.\][asy]
