advanced.solution:
We let $\mathbf{a}$ denote $\overrightarrow{A},$ etc.  Then
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{d} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{c}, \\
\mathbf{e} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{c}, \\
\mathbf{f} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{b}, \\
\mathbf{p} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{d} = \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{c}, \\
\mathbf{q} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{e} = \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{c}, \\
\mathbf{r} &= \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{e} = \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{4} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{c}.
\end{align*}[asy]
unitsize(0.8 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, P, Q, R;

A = (2,5);
B = (0,0);
C = (6,0);
D = (B + C)/2;
E = (A + C)/2;
F = (A + B)/2;
P = (A + D)/2;
Q = (B + E)/2;
