\[\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 13 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} -6 \\ 9 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}\]is a scalar multiple of $\mathbf{a},$ and therefore orthogonal to $\mathbf{b}.$  Hence, $\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{b}} \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 13 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -6 \\ 9 \end{pmatrix}}.$

Let $p_k$ denote the complex number corresponding to the point $P_k,$ for $1 \le k \le 10.$  Since the $P_k$ form a regular decagon centered at 2, the $p_k$ are the roots of
\[(z - 2)^{10} = 1.\]Hence,
\[(z - p_1)(z - p_2)(z - p_3) \dotsm (z - p_{10}) = (z - 2)^{10} - 1.\]By Vieta's formulas, $p_1 p_2 p_3 \dotsm p_{10} = 2^{10} - 1 = \boxed{1023}.$

